  "title": "Assistant Service Engineer (IAP)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li> Perform technical maintenance and troubleshoot Industrial Automation and Control Systems (IACS) to ensure optimal functionality and high uptime.</li><li>Assist in Factory Acceptance Testing (FAT) for control panels, including loop testing, thermocouple testing, and verifying hardware compliance.</li><li> Support senior engineers with designing, assembling, and testing machines and control systems.</li><li>Prepare reports, update maintenance records, and document technical data in accordance with quality standards.</li><li>Act as a point of contact for technical inquiries, providing on-site support and responding to operational incidents.</li><li>Adhere to Workplace Safety and Health (WSH) procedures.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Min Nitec in Electrical Engineering, Electronic Engineering, Computer Engineering, or related fields</li><li>Knowledge of PLC programming (e.g., Rockwell Automation RSLogix 5000), SCADA systems, or Human Machine Interfaces (HMI).</li></ul><p>To submit your application, please apply online to <a href=\"mailto:apply@rn-care.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>apply@rn-care.com </strong></a>or call <strong>+(65) </strong><a href=\"tel:6513 5697\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>6513 5697</strong></a> for private and confidential discussion.</p><p>Your interest will be treated with the strictest of confidence. We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified or contacted.</p><p><strong>RN Care Pte. Ltd</strong><br /><strong>EA License No: 17C8900</strong></p>",
